parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal does not respond
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake system makes unusual noises
the vehicle lurches forward when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not respond
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake system makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Sensor Block and Relay Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake sensor block and relay can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal does not respond
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seatbelt Failure due to Degradation of Plastic Housing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The degradation of the plastic housing of the seatbelts can cause the internal parts to fail, leading to a loss of protection in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or even death.
symptoms: Cracks or brittleness in the plastic housing of the seatbelts
failure of the internal parts of the seatbelt assembly
reduced or complete loss of seatbelt function.
